<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-94-0328 </DOCNO><TEXT>The results of studies on relativistic electron microbeam shaping in electronlinacs for solution of some physical problems such as simulation of radiationdamages of materials, colliding beam experiments, etc. are presented.The technique for production of dense small-size beams consists in preciseadjustment of quadrupole lenses along the beam axis, cutting-off a partof a beam with small emittance and short-focus compression by means ofa douplet of the quadrupole lenses. Long-term (tens of hours) stabilityof parameters of the shaped high-energy electron microbeams for expresssimulation of radiation damages of reactor materials may be assured inelectron linacs. 8 refs.; 2 figs.; 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>